race.comment: URQUHARTS BLUFF (4) was too good last start over 1200m here in a CL1 and rates highly on the back of that effort. He was an odds on chance there and he looks a progressive type on the way up. Maps beautifully and can bring up back-to-back wins. SNIPPY WHICH (2) got a long way back last start but and never really featured in a stronger race last time out. The form out of that race has been strong and he was competitive in similar races to this prior. CJP hops back on board today and he can bounce back to his best. CANNYKEV (6) missed last start when leading at Pinjarra following a 0.7L win two back. Cooper claims 2kg today and the draw should see him one the speed. Can be in this for a very long way. ROMMEL'S GODDESS (9) has gone to another level since joining the Barton stable and she can continue to rise through the grades.
